States Weekly: January 7, 2026

![Photo: CSIS](data:image/png;base64,)

Newsletter by [**Aryan D'Rozario**](https://www.csis.org/people/aryan-drozario) Published January 7, 2026

**Big News: Gujarat** imposes guidelines for **mental health policies focused on students; Delhi** revokes **pollutioncurbs imposed under the Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP) Stage III; Maharashtra** approves the **Maharashtra Industries, Investment and Services Policy, 2025; Rajasthan** approves an **Artificial Intelligence - Machine Learning (AI ML) Policy; Chhattisgarh** amends its **Industrial Development Policy, 2024-30**.**; and more.**

# Health

**Delhi** expands healthcare facilities for the **economically weaker sections (EWS) of society**. According to the Directorate General of Health Services (DGHS), the annual family income limit for receiving free treatment at private hospitals built on subsidized land allotted by the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) has been increased from \$2,443 to \$5,552 (INR 2.20 lakh to INR 5 lakh).

**Source:** [ETV](https://www.etvbharat.com/en/health/delhi-raises-income-limit-for-free-treatment-at-private-hospitals-to-rs-5-lpa-enn26010301625)

**Gujarat** imposes guidelines for **mental health policies focused on students**. The Education Department has issued comprehensive guidelines for all universities,

colleges, and private coaching institutes to implement a formal Mental Health Policy and strengthen student counseling systems.

**Source:** [Bhaskar](https://www.bhaskarenglish.in/local/gujarat/news/gujarat-tightens-rules-to-curb-student-suicides-mandatory-mental-health-policy-counsellors-coaching-curbs-ordered-136805803.html)

**In detail:** [Govt circular](https://education.gujarat.gov.in/ViewFile?fileName=hZ2E6qsHASH_HASHfKX8ui6gIvya9PY32xOIpzHASH__HASHBDjft9a0w0xojpuxZ6aMcCkjtXVvywtmDiStlbDGLBeprFMRGN0ROZ47LmdijR2VFMJOFkYksHA5UXNU3tEyPa2HASH_HASHylbKHIvm1Je1oq9bIPttc8R9HASH__HASHHASH_HASH1oaPg%3D%3D)

**Rajasthan** expands **cashless treatments beyond state borders**. The state announces that residents can now benefit from free and cashless treatment anywhere in India under the 'Mukhyamantri Ayushman Arogya' (Chief Minister's Health Scheme). This health initiative has expanded to include more than 30,000 hospitals across the country.

**Source:** [Devdiscourse](https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/health/3748797-rajasthan-expands-healthcare-horizon-with-nationwide-free-treatment)

**In detail:**[CMO Press release](https://cmo.rajasthan.gov.in/pressreleasedetail/231372)

**Assam** issues a **new framework for the procurement of medical equipment**. An executive order issued by the Finance Department under the Assam Public Procurement Act, 2017, mandates that all medical equipment purchases must be made through the "Government e-Marketplace" (GeM).

**Source:**[Sentinel](https://www.sentinelassam.com/topheadlines/assam-government-issues-new-guidelines-for-medical-equipment-procurement)

**In detail:**[Finance department Order](https://finance.assam.gov.in/sites/default/files/swf_utility_folder/departments/agriculture_com_oid_2/menu/document/executive_order_for_procurement_of_medical_equipment.pdf)

**Kerala** launches **'Arogyam Anandam' (Vibe for Wellness)**. The scheme seeks to spread awareness in four crucial areas - adopting healthy eating habits, encouraging regular physical exercise, ensuring adequate sleep and rest, and fostering mental wellness. The program will be rolled out through 5,416 public health centers across the state.

**Source:**[New Indian Express](https://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/thiruvananthapuram/2026/Jan/02/kerala-health-department-pushes-for-preventive-healthcare-with-arogyam-anandam)

# Climate Change and Energy

**Delhi** revokes **pollutioncurbs imposed under the Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP) Stage III**. The Commission for Air Quality Management (CAQM) states that air quality has improved in the National Capital Region (NCR) of Delhi, and curbs can now be rolled back. The ban on non-essential diesel-run vehicles has

been withdrawn, and the transport of construction materials, including cement, sand and fly ash, is now permitted. Construction activities can also resume.

**Source:** [Hindu Business Line](https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/government-revokes-grap-iii-as-air-pollution-lowers-in-delhi-ncr/article70464956.ece)

**In detail:** [GRAP order](https://caqm.nic.in/WriteReadData/LINKS/GRAP%20Order%20dt%2002012026347bd272-a868-424c-9c25-1cedf133e51f.pdf)

**Rajasthan** approves its **Rajasthan Vehicle Scrapping Policy-2025 (RVSP)**. The policy aims to phase out unfit, old, and polluting vehicles by oï¬€ering rebates to vehicle owners.

**Source:** [Indian Express](https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/jaipur/rajasthan-cabinet-approves-vehicle-scrapping-policy-to-phase-out-polluting-vehicles-10447460/)

**In detail:** [Rajasthan Vehicle Scrapping Policy 2025](https://transport.rajasthan.gov.in/content/dam/transport/transport-dept/pdf/Policies/Registered_Vehicle_Scrapping_Policyfinal%2009_1760099645495-1.pdf)

**Rajasthan** implements a **"Green Credit Policy."** As per the policy, investments in environmental projects will receive credit vouchers of up to 10 percent and benefits of up to \$300,000 (INR 2.5 crore).

**Source:** [Patrika](https://www.patrika.com/en/jaipur-news/rajasthan-green-credit-policy-good-news-green-credit-policy-implemented-in-rajasthan-know-how-to-benefit-20228399)

**In detail:** [Rajasthan Finance Department order](https://finance.rajasthan.gov.in/PDFDOCS/TAX/CCT/14791.pdf)

**Uttar Pradesh** reduces the **cost of smart prepaid meters**. The Uttar Pradesh Electricity Regulatory Commission (UPERC) reduced the costs of smart prepaid meters in its revised Cost Data Book (CDB), 2025. The regulator has fixed the cost at

\$31 (INR 2,800) for single-phase smart prepaid meters and \$45.5 (INR 4,100) for three-phase ones.

**Source:** [Times of India](https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/lucknow/smart-prepaid-meter-cost-in-up-slashed-to-rs-2800/articleshow/126278050.cms)

**In detail:** [UPERC Press release](https://www.uperc.org/App_File/PressNoteCDB-2025-pdf1231202553502PM.pdf)

# Finance

Nothing critical to report this week.

# Industrial Policy and Business Regulations

**Bihar** extends the **Bihar Industrial Area Development Authority's (BIADA) Amnesty Policy, 2025.** The policy has been extended by three months, until

March 31, 2026. The amnesty scheme, which was originally set to expire on December 31, 2025, was introduced to revive closed industrial units, improve utilization of industrial land, and settle long-pending disputes and litigation between entrepreneurs and the state's industrial development authority.

**Source:** [Patna Press](https://patnapress.com/bihar-biada-amnesty-policy-extension-march-2026/)

**In detail:** [Notification](https://biada1.bihar.gov.in/UploadFile/LatestNews/2026/Jan/01-Jan-2026/IMG_d39d27e7-a34b-4246-9df3-737e36ea8dae.pdf)

**Maharashtra** approves the **Maharashtra Industries, Investment and Services Policy, 2025**. The new policy has a strong focus on enhanced competitiveness through improved capital efficiency and reforms. The government aims to establish Maharashtra as a Global Business Destination (GBD) by driving "climate-smart industrialization" and strengthening manufacturing and services.

**Source:** [Hindu Business Line](https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/maharashtras-new-policy-targets-705-lakh-crore-investment/article70460402.ece)

**In detail:** [Maharashtra Industries, Investment & Services Policy 2025](https://gr.maharashtra.gov.in/Site/Upload/Government%20Resolutions/English/202512311332497910.....pdf)

**Rajasthan** approves an **Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning (AI ML) Policy**. The policy aims to make public service delivery faster, transparent, and citizen-centric, enhance administrative efficiency, and encourage innovation-driven economic growth through the responsible, ethical, and secure use of artificial intelligence and machine learning.

**Source:** [Indian Express](https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/jaipur/rajasthan-cabinet-approves-vehicle-scrapping-policy-to-phase-out-polluting-vehicles-10447460/)

**In detail:** [Cabinet decisions](https://cmo.rajasthan.gov.in/pressreleasedetail/231202)

**Jammu and Kashmir** publishes a **draftamendment to its** I**ndustrial Policy, 2021-30.** According to the proposed amendments, sick industries being targeted for revival will receive the same incentives as new industrial units under the policy. Several other subsidies for women-led business have also been proposed.

**Source:** [Kashmir life](https://kashmirlife.net/jammu-kashmir-govt-proposes-incentives-to-revive-sick-units-boost-green-tech-419598/)

**Tripura** unveils the **Tripura RAMP Transport Incentive Scheme, 2025 and the Tripura RAMP Partial Reimbursement of Loan Incentive Scheme, 2025**. The schemes propose reimbursing Mirco, Small, and Medium Enterprises (MSMEs) 50

percent of expenses incurred in moving secondary raw materials and packaging materials from the seller's nearest railway station to the buyer's location. MSMEs participating in state, national, and international fairs will also be eligible for 50 percent reimbursement of travel and transport costs, capped at \$1100 (INR 1 lakh) per participation. The primary objective of both of these schemes is to reduce transportation-related costs faced by Tripura's MSME units.

**Source:** [North East Today](https://northeasttoday.in/northeast/minister-santana-chakma-launches-ramp-incentive-schemes-to-strengthen-tripuras-msme-sector/)

# Land Acquisition and Labor Regulations

**Andhra Pradesh** removes **five categories of land from the prohibited properties list under Section 22-A of the Registration Act**. The new policy aims to ease the burden on landowners who may not have sufficient documents to prove ownership. Lands allotted to ex-servicemen, serving soldiers, freedom fighters, along with lands assigned before June 18, 1954, and private lands have been excluded from the prohibited properties list.

**Source:** [The Hindu](https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/andhra-pradesh-govt-removes-five-categories-of-land-from-the-prohibited-22-a-list/article70460389.ece)

**Goa** issues the **Goa (National Geospatial Knowledge Based) Land Survey of Urban Habitations Rules, 2025.** The rules aim to create accurate digital records of property rights in urban and peri-urban areas across the state.

**Source:** [Digital Goa](https://digitalgoa.com/goa-govt-to-launches-national-geospatial-land-survey-for-urban-areas-rules-notified/)

**In detail:** [Gazette notification](https://goaprintingpress.gov.in/downloads/2526/2526-40-SI-EOG-2.pdf)

# Infrastructure and Governance

**Andhra Pradesh** adds **two new districts**. The two new districts are Polavaram and Markapuram. The state now has 28 districts in total.

**Source:** [The News Minute](https://www.thenewsminute.com/andhra-pradesh/andhra-pradesh-adds-polavaram-and-markapuram-as-two-new-districts)

**In detail:** Order

**Delhi** approves the **Delhi Jan Vishwas (Amendment of Provisions) Bill, 2026.** The bill decriminalizes minor oï¬€enses and promotes "Ease of Doing Business and Ease of Living."

**Source:** [Economic Times](https://legal.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/law-policy/delhi-cabinet-passes-landmark-bill-to-decriminalise-minor-offences/126257171)

**Rajasthan** issues the **Rajasthan Motor Vehicles Aggregator Scheme Rules, 2025**. Cab aggregators, delivery service providers, and e-commerce entities operating in the state will now be required to function under the new rules. The state will determine fares, and at least 80 percent of the fare amount will have to be passed to the driver who is on boarded with the aggregator.

**Source:** [Times of India](https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/jaipur/gig-workers-get-policy-backing-as-raj-implements-new-aggregator-rules/amp_articleshow/126312397.cms)

**In detail:** Rajasthan Motor Vehicles Aggregator Scheme Rules, 2025

**Tamil Nadu** announces the **Tamil Nadu Assured Pension Scheme (TAPS)**. Under the scheme, government employees are assured of a pension amounting to 50 percent of their last drawn monthly salary. Current employees will contribute 10 percent of their salary towards the pension, while the government will contribute the remaining share.

**Source:** [The News Minute](https://www.thenewsminute.com/tamil-nadu/tamil-nadu-launches-assured-pension-scheme-after-23-years-of-demands)

**In detail**: [Press release](https://cms.tn.gov.in/cms_migrated/document/press_release/pr030126_015.pdf) (in Tamil)

**Telangana** revokes its **"two-child norm" policy for Panchayat (local) elections**. The state earlier disqualified individuals with more than two children from contesting rural local body elections.

**Source:** [Times of India](https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/hyderabad/telangana-assembly-passes-bill-to-end-2-child-norm-in-polls/articleshow/126327038.cms)

**Chhattisgarh** amends its **Industrial Development Policy, 2024-30**. The amended policy aims to boost industrial and service sector growth while creating new employment opportunities. Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises (MSME) units in sectors such as pharmaceuticals, textiles, food processing, electronics, artificial intelligence, and information technology, that generate employment for more than 50 persons will be eligible for wage-linked incentives for employing residents of Chhattisgarh,

**Source:** [Economic Times](https://legal.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/law-policy/chhattisgarh-government-enhances-industrial-development-policy-for-2024-30-to-attract-investment/126277339)

**In detail:** [Cabinet decisions](https://cmo.cg.gov.in/cabinet-decisions/31-December-2025%2C-Key-Decisions-of-the-Cabinet-Meeting/VEsyaHJKeSs4RVBjQ0kwUC83Z1NyQT09)

**Goa** creates a **new district**. Kushavati, the new district, will be carved out of South Goa. The state now has three districts - North Goa, South Goa, and Kushavati.

**Source:** [The Goan](https://www.thegoan.net/goa-news/govt-notifies-creation-of-third-district-%E2%80%98kushavati%E2%80%99/141285.html)

**In detail:** Order

**Punjab** extends the deadline for the **Punjab One-Time Settlement (OTS) Scheme for Recovery of Outstanding Dues, 2025.** The new deadline is March 31, 2026. The decision aims to provide relief to traders and industry owners who have been unable to clear tax dues.

**Source:** [Babushahi](https://www.babushahi.com/view-news.php?id=215481)

In detail: One-Time Settlement Scheme

**Punjab** passes the **Punjab Land Revenue (Amendment) Bill, 2025.** The bill seeks to expedite the disposal of cases pending before various revenue authorities under the Punjab Land Revenue Act, 1887.

**Source:**[Times of India](https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/punjab-assembly-oks-3-bills-to-speed-up-revenue-cases-strengthen-property-rights-ease-stamp-duty/articleshow/126258476.cms)

**In detail:**[The Punjab Land Revenue (Amendment) Bill, 2025,](https://cms.neva.gov.in/NeVA/PB/FileStructures/Notices/e131a1ac-d56c-4dff-b0af-d232fbf61132.pdf)

**Punjab** passes **The Punjab Abadi Deh (Record of Rights Amendment) Bill, 2025.** The bill seeks to accelerate the implementation of the 'Mera Ghar Mere Naam' (My House, My Name) scheme to formalize ownership of 'Abadi Deh' lands (inhabited village lands).

**Source:** [Times of India](https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/punjab-assembly-oks-3-bills-to-speed-up-revenue-cases-strengthen-property-rights-ease-stamp-duty/articleshow/126258476.cms)

**In detail:** [The Punjab Land Revenue (Amendment) Bill, 2025,](https://cms.neva.gov.in/NeVA/PB/FileStructures/Notices/e131a1ac-d56c-4dff-b0af-d232fbf61132.pdf)

**Punjab** passes the **Indian Stamp (Punjab Second Amendment) Bill, 2025.** The bill seeks to simplify stamp duty rates. The state aims to make the process more business friendly.

**Source:** [Times of India](https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/punjab-assembly-oks-3-bills-to-speed-up-revenue-cases-strengthen-property-rights-ease-stamp-duty/articleshow/126258476.cms)

**In detail:** [The Indian Stamp (Punjab Second Amendment) Bill, 2025](https://cms.neva.gov.in/NeVA/PB/FileStructures/Notices/18b06fb8-b8ad-4f7b-a02d-6e3ef4ccbbd8.pdf)

# Any Other

**Ladakh** publishes the **Ladakh Sports Policy, 2025.** The policy seeks to establish a Sports Council to focus on talent identification and infrastructure development.

**Source:** [States Times](https://statetimes.in/ladakh-lg-launches-new-sports-policy/)

**In detail:** [Ladakh Sports Policy 2025](https://cdnbbsr.s3waas.gov.in/s395192c98732387165bf8e396c0f2dad2/uploads/2025/03/202503101256039293.pdf)
